Package: openaps-tls-proxy
Version: v1.1.6
Architecture: armv7ahf-vfp-neon
Maintainer: Bolke de Bruin <bdbruin@gmail.com>
Section: net
Priority: optional
Depends:
Description: OpenAPS loopback TLS proxy and opkg feed front-end.
 Terminates a plain-HTTP opkg feed on 127.0.0.1 and upstreams it to the
 GitHub-hosted OpenAPS feed over modern TLS. Verifies the release-key RSA
 signature on the feed index and on every .ipk before opkg sees it, which is
 the only authenticity check on this device (opkg enforces MD5Sum only and
 cannot verify signatures itself). Ships the opkg config that points opkg at
 the proxy and keeps opkg scratch on /home (the 16 MiB /tmp tmpfs overflows).
